The paper discusses the use of online learning algorithms for hiring teams for crowdsourcing projects, which involves tasks that require human computation. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also considers the use of graph structures to improve the learning process, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges faced by recruiters in crowdsourcing, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
